mapas.name: Aniyah Palace
Broadcast
mapas.description: From the atrium and massive newsroom to the station’s balcony and nearby office buildings, this map could cater to serious CQB play through numerous tight corridors. Meanwhile, those using assault rifles, LMGs, marksman rifles, or sniper rifles can counterplay SMGs and shotguns with the use of various sightlines and the limited, yet still viable, verticality on offer.

Take to the townhomes for long sightlines, the stores to capture objectives through intense CQB battles, or take to the side streets to take some shortcuts. If you dare, try to challenge those who may set up shop in second-story windows, phone booths, front yards, or scaffolding.
mapas.name: Chesire Park
Hovec Sawmill
mapas.description: Although this humble community is a beautiful one, don’t let it distract you from the battle. Use rooftops of buildings to gain the high ground against enemies sprinting from building to building below and use the splashes of footsteps on the rolling river to track down flanking players.

mapas.name: Mialstore Tank Factory
mapas.description: For either skirmish size, expect a mix of indoor and outdoor combat zones with two large buildings – the eponymous tank factory and a warehouse – being the map’s central point of conflict due to sheer surface area and accessible rooftops. Other areas to explore include an abandoned workshop, skybridge, scrapyard, shipping area, and residential zone, with some parts of the map sectioned off if it is being used for 6v6 combat.

mapas.location: 14 km outside of El Nadaar, Urzikstan
mapas.name: Rammaza
Station
mapas.description: Every top of the boxcars and passenger car can be climbed on top of, which give superior verticality at the cost of being essentially exposed on all sides. Other objects, such as crates, containers, and even tank parts, can also be used to gain a height advantage or just be used as cover.

In the middle of the Urzikstan desert lies an urban city with a major construction project taking place at its center. With its citizens long evacuated, combat takes place from door-to-door as teams fight for control of the various overlooks and buildings. Prepare for a great mix of close-quarters combat and long-range sniper duels.
